entry.title: Johanna Staude's mouth in her portrait (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Gustav Klimt did not finish painting Johanna Staude's mouth in her portrait (pictured)?

entry.title: Lorenzo White (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Lorenzo White was the first player to rush for 2,000 yards in a season without winning the Heisman Trophy?

entry.title: holmium (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that holmium has the highest magnetic moment of any naturally occurring element?

entry.title: Jorge Medina (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Jorge Medina – the first Afro-Bolivian in parliament – recalled being harassed as a young adult due to the superstitious belief that pinching a black person brought good luck?

entry.title: Earl Hays Press (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the prop currency produced by the Earl Hays Press for the 1965 film The Cincinnati Kid was so realistic that it entered circulation and the plates had to be destroyed by the United States Secret Service?

entry.title: Ice King (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Ice King, the antagonist of television series Adventure Time, was at first received negatively by critics but later praised for representing mental health issues such as Alzheimer's disease?

entry.title: Midtown Theater (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Midtown Theater was nowhere near Midtown?
